cost-effectiveness ratio reaches a value of €32,752.44 per QALY when scenario 1 
is compared with scenario 3.
CONCLUSION: The use of eltrombopag in HCV patients with thrombocytopenia is 
cost-effective as it leads to a reduction in disease progression and thus a drop 
in the number of patients with advanced liver disease.

